subSubSection.paragraph:
Description of genitalia.
Pygophore (
Figs. 10A
, 
17C
) compressed dorsoventrally, hexagonal in ventral view, strongly concave at anterior margin of dorsum, elevated at center of venter, smooth on surface, irregularly punctate in middle part of dorsum. Paramere (
Fig. 18C
) expanded in middle part, curved inward in apical part; outer and inner margins covered with pubescence in middle part. Female terminalia (
Fig. 11A
) pentagonal in ventral view, covered with pubescence.

Host plant.

Causonis japonica
(Thunb.) Raf.

[= 

Cissus japonica
(Thunb.) Willd.

] (
Vitaceae
) (Takeya 1951; 
Miyamoto 1965
, 
2008
; Yamada & Tomokuni 2012; 
Komatsu 2016
; 
Okochi 2019
).

In Japan , adults were observed from April to November ( Miyamoto 1976 ; Yazaki 2009; Yamada & Tomokuni 2012; Yano et al . 2013; Maehara 2014 ;
Nozaki et al . 2015
; Komatsu 2016 ; Ito & Sasaki 2018 ; Okochi 2019 ; present study) and nymphs were collected in June and September (Yamada & Ishikawa 2012; present study). The overwintering stage remains unknown.
